function clean_column(col) {
  return col.toLowerCase().trim().replace(/[ -]/g, '_');
}
```
This function takes a string `col` as input, and returns a new string that is lowercased, has leading and trailing whitespace removed, and replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores. The regular expression `[ -]` matches any space or hyphen characters in the input string, and the `g` flag at the end of the regular expression makes it match all occurrences, not just the first one.
